meanings.definition: To strike or hit more times than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: In the game, the batter outhits the pitcher by hitting the ball multiple times.
meanings.sent2: The baseball player outhits his opponent by consistently hitting the ball farther.
meanings.sent3: The cat outhits the mouse in their playful game of swatting at each other.
meanings.sent4: The student outhits the target in the archery competition, showing great skill.
meanings.sent5: The dancer outhits the rhythm with her precise and energetic movements.

meanings.sent1: The skilled boxer outhits his opponent with quick and powerful punches.
meanings.sent2: The tennis player outhits her rival with accurate and strategic shots.
meanings.sent3: The chef outhits the competition with his flavorful and innovative dishes.
meanings.sent4: The artist outhits expectations with her stunning and unique paintings.
meanings.sent5: The musician outhits the high notes with his melodious and captivating performance.
